(
  'One Prompt, Nine Platforms: The Multi-Platform Prompting Guide for 2026',
  'multi-platform-prompting-guide',
  E'The AI landscape in 2026 is no longer a one-platform world. Professionals across Asia use an average of 3.2 different AI tools daily. ChatGPT for brainstorming. Claude for writing. DeepSeek for Chinese content. MidJourney for visuals. The catch? The same prompt produces wildly different results on each platform.\n\n## Why the Same Prompt Fails on Different Platforms\n\nEach AI model was trained on different data, with different objectives, and with different architectural decisions. GPT models excel at following complex multi-step instructions. Claude shines at nuanced, safe, and thoughtful responses. DeepSeek dominates Chinese-language reasoning. Gemini leverages Google''s multimodal and search integration strengths.\n\nWhen you use the same prompt across platforms without adaptation, you are leaving performance on the table.\n\n## Platform-by-Platform Breakdown\n\n### ChatGPT (OpenAI)\n\n**Best for:** General-purpose tasks, brainstorming, coding, multi-step workflows\n\nChatGPT responds well to system-level framing. Start with "You are a [role]" and provide explicit output format instructions. GPT models handle long, detailed prompts effectively and benefit from chain-of-thought reasoning.\n\n> **PRO TIP:** Use numbered constraints to keep GPT focused. "Follow these 4 rules: 1) Keep under 200 words, 2) Use active voice, 3) Include one statistic, 4) End with a question."\n\n### Claude (Anthropic)\n\n**Best for:** Long-form writing, analysis, careful reasoning, document review\n\nClaude excels with context-heavy prompts. It handles massive context windows (up to 200K tokens) and produces nuanced, well-structured long-form content. Be specific about tone and audience.\n\n### Gemini (Google)\n\n**Best for:** Research, multimodal tasks, Google ecosystem integration\n\nGemini''s strength is multimodal understanding and real-time information access. For Asian markets, Gemini has particularly strong Hindi, Bengali, and ASEAN language support.\n\n### DeepSeek\n\n**Best for:** Chinese-language tasks, code generation, mathematical reasoning\n\nDeepSeek is a powerhouse for Chinese content. Structure prompts in Chinese for best results, and use clear task decomposition.\n\n> **PRO TIP:** For DeepSeek, prompting in Chinese (even for tasks that will produce English output) often yields better structured and more culturally aware results for Asian markets.\n\n### Qwen (Alibaba)\n\n**Best for:** E-commerce content, Chinese business contexts, product descriptions\n\nBuilt by Alibaba, Qwen understands Asian e-commerce deeply. For Taobao, Tmall, or cross-border e-commerce content, Qwen produces the most authentic and conversion-oriented copy.\n\n### Ernie Bot (Baidu)\n\n**Best for:** Chinese SEO, Baidu-optimized content, Chinese social media\n\nErnie Bot is purpose-built for the Baidu ecosystem. If your content needs to rank on Baidu or perform on WeChat, Xiaohongshu, or Douyin, Ernie understands the content patterns that work.\n\n### MidJourney\n\n**Best for:** Image generation, visual content, creative direction\n\nMidJourney prompts work best with comma-separated descriptors rather than full sentences. For Asian aesthetics, reference specific art styles (ukiyo-e, Chinese ink wash, K-drama cinematography).\n\n### Perplexity\n\n**Best for:** Research, fact-checking, cited answers, market analysis\n\nPerplexity is a research-first AI. Frame your prompts as research questions rather than creative tasks. Ask for sources, comparisons, and data-backed answers.\n\n## The Universal Prompt Framework\n\n1. **Role:** Define who the AI should be\n2. **Context:** Provide background\n3. **Task:** State exactly what you need\n4. **Format:** Specify the output structure\n5. **Constraints:** Set boundaries\n\n## Platform Selection by Use Case\n\n| Use Case | Best Platform | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| Chinese e-commerce copy | Qwen / Ernie | Native marketplace understanding |\n| Japanese business emails | Claude / ChatGPT | Strong keigo handling |\n| ASEAN social media | ChatGPT / Gemini | Broad language coverage |\n| Market research (Asia) | Perplexity | Cited, current data |\n| Visual content | MidJourney | Superior image quality |\n| Code + Chinese docs | DeepSeek | Best CJK + code combo |\n| Long-form analysis | Claude | 200K context window |\n\n## Stop Guessing. Start Optimizing.\n\nThe era of "one prompt fits all" is over. In 2026, the professionals who get the best AI results are the ones who understand which platform to use, how to tailor their prompts, and when to switch tools.\n\nPromptAndGo is the only tool that optimizes your prompts for all nine major platforms simultaneously.',
  'ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, DeepSeek, Qwen, Ernie, MidJourney, Perplexity, and Baidu all respond differently to the same prompt. Learn how to tailor your prompts for each platform.',
  'Master multi-platform AI prompting for ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, DeepSeek, Qwen, and more. The complete 2026 guide to optimizing prompts across 9 platforms.',
